The paper deals with the study of the number of repeats in words of fixed length, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of gapped repeats is related to combinatorics (cs.CC) and the study of algorithms for finding such repeats can be classified under data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of upper bounds, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and the use of probabilistic methods, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
